Consistent, fresh ingredients and kind workers. I've been to several locations but this one seems to be one of my favorites!! Unlimited healthy buffet for less than $10?! YES PLEASE!!!
I come here once a week for lunch because the food is always fresh and the staff are ALWAYS friendly.
Always always always yummy. One of my favorite spots!!
Great food, but after lunch hours.... they don't even bother to keep their soups warm.
Good spot for soup and a sandwich

I remember how we used to go to Hale and Hearty, that is, my co-workers and I for soup and salad during the winter months. One of my co-workers went so much as using this place as her healthy food place. She did lose some weight. The variety of soup did it for me. That split pea soup....Try it. Yes, I got the piece of bread. I couldn't resist.
Friendly staff. Nice salads
Favorite place ever! Never had a soup I didn't like even when the combinations seem odd.  Great for vegetarians!!!
Coconut Shrimp and Mango lime Chicken Salad....yummy!!!
Amazing fresh salads and hot soups, their pair combo is an awesome price especially compared to other nearby places. Customer service is amazing, and the employees are always smiley and courteous.

Expensive. Very expensive. Chili is about equal yo Wendy's chili. These 5 stars are for the service and for the Cauliflower Cheddar soup which I haven't seen in a while. Take advantage of their policy of letting customers taste soups because not doing that is how I wound up with their chili.
Soup was hot and tasty, sandwich fresh and warm. Counterperson polite and friendly. Clean and plenty of seating.  This will be my new downtown spot after work. Though they close their doors at 5pm.
Nice and tasty
Soup Missing from Order, was not redelivered after repeated phone calls and failed promises, manager was abrupt
Love it
Large selection of soups
Great place for lunch. Good lunch options for a very reasonable price and good quality food. Occasional seasonal specials will give more bang for the buck. Great staff in this location.
Fancy fast food. Soups, everybody likes soup.   Do yourself a favor and have a soup.

The food here is very good. The salads are made fresh in front of you. Everything is very light but very filling. I was pleasantly surprised. The staff here is very very nice. It is definitely one of the best salads I have honestly ever eaten in my life. I would definitely suggest that you look up the menu before you go in. The line moves fast and if you are not sure what you want by the time you get up to the counter then you are going to be having issues.. Wish they had a location up by me.
Yay soup! If only they had italian wedding soup every day
Love this place. Cheap and always tastey!

The service here is terrible.  Forty-five minutes after the food was due to be delivered, it still had not arrived.  Moreover, customer service lied about the food being "on it's way."  Clearly, "food service industry" does not describe this location.  Additionally, this is the second time this happened.  Live and learn.

Great option for lunch.  Vast variety of flavors and the restaurant has plenty of seating.  Expect to spend at least 8 to 10 dollars if you plan on having a drink with your soup depending on what size you order.
Good selections but always so crowned and expensive
Nothing amazing.

I have a personal jazz bucket list and the Blue Note has helped me check off quite a few world class artists. Don't come for the atmosphere. Be prepared to sit shoulder to shoulder inbetween clueless tourists and loyal jazz patrons. Eat before the show or have a liquid dinner. Also be prepared for the minimums because you will be spending some money, honey.  Ok, why do I like this place again? The jazz! We do it for the jazz!
Average soup.

The other dishes are average in my opinion... but the soup dumplings are amazing! I also really like the beef noodle soup here. A very casual spot good to have dinner with friends.  There is a huge packing lot right next to this place so you don't have to worry about not finding a parking space.
Quite ok place to have warming soup on cold winter day.

I like to come after the lunch time rush. Although it can get a bit crowded the lines move fast and the people that work there are always so nice and professional. Almost every Hale and Hearty I've been to the people know what they're doing. I think they have one of the best customer service here. Also the soups are always good and you really can't go wrong especially on a cold winter day.
Yes it's a chain, but it's a decent, quick option near the court I used to work at. Super crazy during lunch.

Great homemade soups. Large selection every day. I believe they still have the lunch special: bowl of soup, pretzel roll, and a beverage. The pretzel roll is interesting. Hot, crunchy on the outside and chewy and warm on the inside. Great combo. The soups are delicious. Self service. Service is good. Prices are cheap.
Great soup
